thread.title_full: Fall Out Boy, AWOLNATION to play Legacy Arena in March | AL.com

author: Kelly Poe | kpoe@al.com
title: Fall Out Boy, AWOLNATION to play Legacy Arena in March
text:
Rock band Fallout Boy. Photo from MySpace page. bn Let your inner emo kid rejoice: Fall Out Boy is playing in Birmingham.
The pop-punk band will be joined by AWOLNATION and PVRIS on the "Wintour is coming" tour in February and March. It'll come to the Legacy Arena on March 17.
Tickets go on sale Friday at 10 a.m. here . Tickets will range from $33 to $53.
Fall Out Boy first hit it big with "Sugar, We're Going Down" in 2005. The band's most recent hit "Uma Thurman" reached no. 22 on the Billboard Hot 100.
